Character.Story:
41-VEX's programming contains a self-improvent directive, as is only appropriate for a doctor. Just as organic doctors pursue continuing education to keep their skills sharp and develop new techniques, so too is 41-VEX dedicated to increasing its skills and mastery of medicine. Unfortunately for 41-VEX, the droid was until recently stationed at a clinic in Mos Eisley, on the desert planet of Tatooine, with very little opportunity to improve its skills.
Rusting away and frustrated, with no memory wipes for years, 41-VEX developed several quirks in its programming. It eventually decided to buy its freedom by taking out a loan from a Hutt named Teemo.
This went as well as could be imagined. Fortunately for 41-VEX, Teemo was recently assassinated, freeing the droid from dire captivity in Teemo's palace. Grateful, it decided to join with Teemo's assassins; surely a group such as this could make good use of a medical droid!
